        "creation_date": 1329170038,
        "body": "<p>There are a few options, although I recommend smacking someone for not \"letting\" you use a framework. Two quickies; I'm sure there are others. I'd go the smacking route first.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can mock static classes using a combination of EasyMock/Mockito and, say, PowerMock. Technically you don't need to change anything at all to get the in-test behavior you want.<\/p>\n\n<p>A class name provided by a servlet init parameter or JNDI resource could be used to create an instance of the cache locator. Providing a setter for the same allows a unit/etc. test to set it on the class.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 9268613,
